Adjust rack to top position and heat broiler to high. Line a #baking sheet{} with foil. Wash and dry produce.

Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens.

Pat @Standard Meat™ Cast-Iron Seared Chicken Breasts{9%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}. Thinly slice crosswise into strips.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon} in a #medium pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken, scallion whites, and @Southwest Spice Blend{1%tablespoon}. Cook until chicken is warmed through and scallions are slightly softened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Rub one side of each @flour tortillas{2} with a drizzle of @vegetable oil{2%teaspoon}. Place tortillas oiled sides down on prepared baking sheet.

Evenly sprinkle @pepper jack cheese{1/2%cup} onto one half of each tortilla. Top with chicken mixture, then sprinkle with @Monterey Jack cheese{1/4%cup}. Fold tortillas in half to create quesadillas.

Broil quesadillas on top rack until golden brown, ~{1-2%minutes} per side.

Cut quesadillas into wedges and divide between plates. Sprinkle with scallion greens and drizzle with @hot sauce{1%teaspoon} if desired. Serve with @smoky red pepper crema{4%tablespoon} on the side.